# Modpack Import UI Walkthrough

## Changes
- **Backend**: Updated [ModpackService.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/Ecosystem/ModpackService.cs) to support `IProgress<double>` and `IProgress<string>` for real-time feedback.
- **Frontend**: 
    - Added "Import .mrpack" button to [ResourcesPage.xaml](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/ResourcesPage.xaml).
    - Implemented a full-screen semi-transparent **Progress Overlay** in [ResourcesPage.xaml](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/ResourcesPage.xaml) that blocks interaction during import.
- **ViewModel**: Added `IsImporting` state and `ImportModpackCommand` in [ResourcesViewModel.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/ViewModels/ResourcesViewModel.cs) to orchestrate the process.

## Verification Results

### 1. Import Button
- [x] Verified "Import .mrpack" button appears in the Resources page header.
- [x] Verified clicking it opens the file picker filter for `*.mrpack`.

### 2. Import Process
- [x] Validated that selecting a file triggers the **Progress Overlay**.
- [x] Verified the overlay shows:
    - "Importing Modpack" title.
    - Progress bar updating with file extraction/download.
    - Status text showing current operation (e.g., "Downloading sodium-fabric.jar (2/50)...").

### 3. Completion
- [x] Verified success message box appears after completion.
- [x] Verified error message box appears if file is invalid or download fails.
- [x] Verified the new version folder is created in `.minecraft/versions/`.

## Next Steps
- Implement **Modloader Installer** to ensure the imported pack has the correct Fabric/Forge loader installed (currently it might rely on an existing installation or manual setup).
